Existing pavement is considered to be in reasonable condition and does not require major rehabilitation works at this time.  
This is the last stage of widening between Loddon Valley Hwy and Shire Boundary along Bridgewater Raywood rd and offers the least benefit from either a safety or asset preservation standpoint.  Proposal is to widen (only) the existing pavement to create a 6.2m seal and treat the existing pavement with a reseal.  Historically this section of road has a medium to high maintenance effort for edge repairs and some crack sealing.
